From: Nick <nick@local>
Subject: [PATCH] media: jaguar2: assign MIPI CSI-2 virtual channels per input

Map NVP6324 input channels to distinct MIPI CSI-2 virtual channels
(ch0->VC0, ch1->VC1, ch2->VC2, ch3->VC3) via Bank 0x21 register 0x0E.

Write the VC assignment register BEFORE enabling the MIPI TX (reg 0x44),
so the hardware latches the VC configuration at enable time. Writing
after enable causes the assignment to be ignored — only VC0 works.

Without this, all 4 channels are multiplexed on VC0 and only one
CIF stream ID receives frames. The rkcif driver filters by VC per
video device node, so proper VC tagging is required for simultaneous
multi-stream capture.

---
 drivers/media/i2c/jaguar2_drv/jaguar2_mipi.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/media/i2c/jaguar2_drv/jaguar2_mipi.c b/drivers/media/i2c/jaguar2_drv/jaguar2_mipi.c
--- a/drivers/media/i2c/jaguar2_drv/jaguar2_mipi.c
+++ b/drivers/media/i2c/jaguar2_drv/jaguar2_mipi.c
@@ -270,7 +270,14 @@ void mipi_tx_init2(int dev_num)
 	// MIPI setting
 	gpio_i2c_write(jaguar2_i2c_addr[dev_num], 0x44, 0x00);
 	gpio_i2c_write(jaguar2_i2c_addr[dev_num], 0x49, 0xF3);
 	gpio_i2c_write(jaguar2_i2c_addr[dev_num], 0x49, 0xF0);
+
+	// Virtual channel assignment: ch0->VC0, ch1->VC1, ch2->VC2, ch3->VC3
+	// Register 0x0E bits[1:0]=0, [3:2]=1, [5:4]=2, [7:6]=3 = 0xE4
+	// Must be written BEFORE MIPI TX enable (0x44=0x02) so HW latches it
+	gpio_i2c_write(jaguar2_i2c_addr[dev_num], 0x0E, 0xE4);
+	pr_info("[DRV] MIPI TX VC assignment: 0xE4 (ch0-3 -> VC0-3)\n");
+
 	gpio_i2c_write(jaguar2_i2c_addr[dev_num], 0x44, 0x02);
 
 	gpio_i2c_write(jaguar2_i2c_addr[dev_num], 0x08, 0x40);
